(1)
92-76 Roosevelt Street, east side, at Batavia Street. -Shown on the extreme right, is a portion of the 6-story apartment house, Nos. 92-94. Adjoining same and north to the S.E. corner of Batavia Street, are Nos. 88 to 84. On the extreme left, are Nos. 78-76, at and adjoining the S.E. corner of Batavia Street.
September 9, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, showing a front view of Nos. 84 to 88 Roosevelt Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Batavia Street.
April 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same as No. 2, slightly southward, showing the 6-story building Nos. 90-92.
April 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

Roosevelt Street, east side, at Batavia Street. Also shown is Batavia Street, east to and including James Street. The portion of building shown at the end of Batavia Street, is P.S. No. 114 (East Side Continuation School).

April 25, 1934.
